-- LED Maker Bridgelux Gets $25 Million Investment From Kaistar
-- B y   A n d r e w   H e r n d o n
-- 2012-02-13T21:06:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/led-maker-bridgelux-gets-25-million-investment-from-kaistar.html
Bridgelux Inc., a closely held maker
of light-emitting diodes, received a $25 million investment from
Kaistar Lighting Xiamen Co., a joint venture of two Chinese
manufacturers.  The funding will be used to develop LED chip and packaging
technology for general lighting, Livermore, California-based
Bridgelux said today in a statement.   Kaistar is a venture of the LED chip and wafer maker
 Epistar Corp. (2448)  and the contract manufacturer Shenzhen Kaifa
Technology Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Herndon in San Francisco at 
 aherndon2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  